description: Middle English, from Old Norse dasaðr (“weary”), dasask (“to become weary”), from Proto-Germanic *dasōjan-, from the adjective *daza-, possibly from a variant of Proto-Indo-European *dʰer- (“to hold, support”), related to Armenian դադարել (dadarel, “to settle, stop, end”).

adjectives.description: dazed (comparative more dazed, superlative most dazed)

entries.meaning: In a state of shock or confusion.
simple past tense and past participle of daze
